<HEADLINE>
NEED FOR RELIEF COSTS CUBS' WOOD $90 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By MONICA DAVIS  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Chicago Cubs pitcher Kerry Wood earned a visit from
police and a date in court for recently urinating in public.
</P>
<P>
   Police spotted Wood, 21, and his friend, Kevin Walker, 22, a
pitcher in the San Diego Padres organization, about 1:10 a.m. on
Feb. 13 in the 7300 block of East Stetson Drive.
</P>
<P>
   When the bicycle officers approached, Wood told Officer Brian
Brown, ``I can't stop now, I have to finish.''
</P>
<P>
   Wood then asked about the amount of the fine.
</P>
<P>
   Brown described Wood as cooperative, but Officer Jennifer Clair
had harsher words for Walker, who also was cited for urinating in
public.
</P>
<P>
   Clair said Walker was cooperative but sarcastic. She also
described him as intoxicated.
</P>
<P>
   Clair said Wood seemed to offer an apology at one point by
saying, ``We weren't very secretive.''
</P>
<P>
   Walker then reportedly added, ``I would have done it, anyway.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Wood appeared in Scottsdale Municipal Court last Friday and
pleaded no contest to urinating in public, said Pat Dunn, deputy
court administrator.
</P>
<P>
   She said he was found guilty and fined $90.
</P>
<P>
   Walker missed his court appearance, leading officials to issue a
warrant for his arrest, Dunn said.
</P>
<P>
   Doug Dirren, a Scottsdale police spokesman, said the officers
found Wood and Walker in a popular area.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's in the hub of the city's entertainment district,'' he
said. ``Nightclubs. Restaurants.''
</P>
<P>
   Dirren did not know where the two had been before being spotted
by officers.
</P>
<P>
   Wood, the 1998 National League Rookie of the Year, won't play
for the Cubs this year. He suffered a full ligament tear in his
right elbow on Saturday during his first spring appearance.
</P>
<P>
   Neither Wood nor Walker could be reached for comment. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-19-99 0208EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
