<HEADER>
A6264 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKC-WEST-NOTEBOOK-AZR     03-19 1087
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-WEST-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NOTES FROM THE WEST REGIONAL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By THE ARIZONA REPUBLIC  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; OLD FRIENDS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   One notable Gonzaga fan celebrating at America West Arena was
former Michigan State Coach &UR; Jud Heathcote.
</P>
<P>
   Heathcote, whose Magic Johnson-led Spartans won the national
championship in 1979, goes back a long way with Bulldogs Coach  &UR; Dan
 &UR; Monson.
</P>
<P>
   ``I knew Dan when he was born,'' Heathcote said after Gonzaga's
73-73 victory over Florida to advance to Saturday's West Region
finals.
</P>
<P>
   Dan Monson's dad, &UR; Don, was Heathcote's assistant and the two
have remained the best of friends. Both live in Spokane, Wash.,
home to Gonzaga.
</P>
<P>
   ``I go to all the games,'' Heathcote said. ``When you live in
Spokane, they're the only Division I team there.''
</P>
<P>
   Heathcote wasn't going bonkers like those seated around him, but
he looked just as happy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, it's just fantastic,'' he said. ``I guess you can call
'em Cinderella, but it's a good basketball team. Has been all
year.'' &QL; 
 &UR; LET THE BIDDING BEGIN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   When Arizona State bid to host the 2002 or 2003 West Regional at
America West Arena, Sun Devils officials were turned down because
they and arena officials refused to guarantee that all of the
signage at the arena would be covered during the event.
</P>
<P>
   They have reversed that policy, and as a result, plan to bid in
two years for the West Regional in 2004 and 2005.
</P>
<P>
   The signage rule wasn't in effect when Phoenix was awarded the
1999 West Regional.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Bill Hancock, NCAA director of men's championships and a member
of the basketball committee, said he was impressed by the job
Phoenix has done in hosting its first West Regional.
</P>
<P>
   ``They've done a great job,'' Hancock said. ``They ought to be a
(West Regional) site in the future.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Herman Frazier, senior associate athletic director at ASU, said
the school and the arena definitely will bid again.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're aggressive around here at going after events and it's
the thing we should do,'' Frazier said.
</P>
<P>
   The wait for the next NCAA tournament games to be held in
Arizona won't be long. First- and second-round West subregional
games will be played at McKale Center in Tucson next March. &QL; 
 &UR; GOING DEEP &QL; 
Just a few weeks ago, Connecticut Coach  &UR; Jim Calhoun committed
himself to using his bench more. ``We said, `We had to get back to
who we are,' '' he said. ``We've made a concerted effort to make
sure we keep (Khalid) El-Amin and Rip (Richard Hamilton) to about
28 to 30 minutes.'' &QL; 
 &UR; GLASS SLIPPER &QL; 
Gonzaga is the first West Coast Conference team to reach the Elite
Eight since Loyola Marymount did so in 1990. That's where Loyola's
journey ended.
</P>
<P>
   The Bulldogs aren't looking for midnight. Actually, they're
getting tired of all the Cinderella references.
</P>
<P>
   After Casey Calvary tipped in the game-winning basket, he told a
national television audience: ``Richie Frahm had the best quote:
`Whoever hands us the glass slipper, we're going to bash them over
the head with it.' '' &QL; 
 &UR; GRACE UNDER PRESSURE &QL; 
Gonzaga guard Matt Santangelo, who had the hot hand in the first
two rounds of the regional, had a subpar shooting night Thursday.
He made 3 of 13 shots, 2 of 6 from three-point range, and finished
with 11 points.
</P>
<P>
   But Florida guard Teddy Dupay said he thought Santangelo's poise
under the Gators' full-court pressure was the main reason Gonzaga
won.
</P>
<P>
   Santangelo had seven assists and three turnovers. Point guard
Quentin Hall had six turnovers and four assists for the Bulldogs.
</P>
<P>
   ``Santangelo pretty much saved them, I think,'' Dupay said. ``He
did a great job. The other guy (Hall) didn't look too good.
Santangelo is probably going to be a pro, I think. The other guy
talks good ball, but he wasn't too sure out there. He was giving it
up every chance he could out there.'' &QL; 
 &UR; GRACIOUS HOSTS &QL; 
Arizona State didn't get into the NCAA Tournament, much less the
Sweet 16, but the Sun Devils were represented at the West Regional
at America West Arena.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Rob Evans was there, watching, and so were two of his
players, working. Senior guard Ron DuBois and freshman forward Chad
Prewitt volunteered to help out, running statistics to the media
and the official scorer's table.
</P>
<P>
   Evans noted Prewitt's wardrobe.
</P>
<P>
   ``First time he's worn a tie,'' Evans said.
</P>
<P>
   He added, ``With tennis shoes.''
</P>
<P>
   Prewitt, a graduate of Greenway High School, was taking his
knocks.
</P>
<P>
   ``Chad worked real hard,'' associate sports information director
Doug Tammaro said. ``As a matter of fact, I had him running harder
than Rob Evans did all year,''
</P>
<P>
   Tammaro wanted it made clear he was kidding. &QL; 
 &UR; DISCREETLY MISSING &QL; 
Florida freshman forward Mike Miller had 11 rebounds, eight on the
defensive end, but was not in the game at the end when Gonzaga
forward Casey Calvary leaped in for the offensive board and game
winner with four seconds to play.
</P>
<P>
   Miller said it hurt to watch.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't take a more hurting way,'' he said. ``But as bad as
we played and as good as they shot, to be in that situation was a
blessing.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just didn't get the clutch rebound.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HOME COURT 'DOGS? &QL; 
Gonzaga clearly had the crowd advantage against Florida. Bulldogs
Coach Dan Monson said it was reminiscent of last week's games in
Seattle, which isn't far from the school's campus in Spokane, Wash.
</P>
<P>
   Said guard Matt Santangelo, ``I think everybody roots for the
underdog. We have a lot of Gonzaga fans down here. I guess a
busload of students came in before the game and they were hassling
the Florida guys. . . . We have a lot of people down here
supporting us, and we are thankful.'' &QL; 
 &UR; BIG CROWD &QL; 
The attendance at America West Arena was 17,975 on Thursday. That
would make it the largest crowd ever to watch a college basketball
game in Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TRIVIA &QL; 
In 1987, Florida Coach &UR; Billy Donovan led unknown Providence to the
Final Four. Who knocked off the Friars in the semifinals? &QL; 
 &UR; NO UPS AND DOWNS &QL; 
One of Calhoun's biggest goals at Connecticut is keeping the
Huskies at the top of the Big East Conference standings each year.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our league is a funny league when you think about it,'' he
said. ``Seton Hall has been to the Final Four and been last place
in our league. Our league has a lot of elevators that go up and
down. You had better make sure that your elevator is always going
up.'' &QL; 
 &UR; TRIVIA ANSWER &QL; 
Syracuse, 77-63. &QL; 
Contributing to this report were staff writers Bob Cohn, Richard
Obert, Steve Schoenfeld and Kent Somers. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
