<P>
   MINTER-COLUMN _ FAYETTE COUNTY, Ga. _ An excerpt from Jim
Minter's book, ``Some Things I Wish We Wouldn't Forget,'' about a
childhood friend realizing his dream of seeing a major league
baseball game. Junior Miles came back with a much more interesting
story than home runs, however. ``In Detroit,'' he told me instead,
``There ain't no black, and there ain't no white.'' (Jim Minter is
a former editor of The Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED FOR
SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ I had thought we'd be electing a president of
the United States next year, not the pastor of the United States,
but much of the Republican field seems to be running for a real
pulpit, not just the bully one. (Tom Teepen is national
correspondent for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED THURSDAY FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ I'm not going out shopping for Y2K. If
whatever is supposed to go down on Jan. 1 does go down, I've got my
leftover supplies from the 1999 hurricane season that ends Dec. 1 _
that is, provided we don't get nailed with a dead-on hurricane as
we did in 1992. Glad we were prepared for that. (Howard Kleinberg
is a columnist for Cox News Service.) MOVED THURSDAY FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
