the Libyan leader Muammar Gadhafi has promised in a letter to the
United Nations to hand over the suspects accused of the bombing
over Lockerbie, Scotland, by April 6. By Paul Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-BOMB (Moscow) _ At least 53 people were killed by a bomb
at a market in North Ossetia, the province adjacent to Chechnya.
The identity of the bombers and their motive was unknown, although
the region has seen much political, ethnic and common criminal
violence. By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   BALLOONISTS (Geneva) _ The round-the-world ballonists have
caught the jet stream again and are traveling briskly across the
Atlantic. They expect to cross the African coast sometime Saturday
and now hope to land in Egypt near the Pyramids early Sunday
morning Egypt time. By Malcolm W. Browne.
</P>
