   With map.
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-EDUCATION (Paris) _ Foreign Journal: Trying to change the
education system in a country that fears any sort of change is a
thankless job, says Claude Allegre, the feisty French minister of
education, with some exasperation. Since his old friend Lionel
Jospin, the prime minister, picked Allegre, 62, to run the vast
French education bureaucracy, he has become one of the most
vilified politicians in France. By Craig R. Whitney.
