<P>
   SERIAL-KILLERS (Orlando, Fla.) _ Jim Larson lost two women he
loved to random killers. First it was his sister, Sonja Larson. She
and a roommate were stabbed to death in 1990 by Danny Rolling, a
serial killer who said demons spoke to him. Then in 1997, Larson's
wife, Carla, was abducted from a supermarket parking lot by a man
on vacation at Disney World. Later this month his wife's killer,
John Huggins, will join Rolling on Florida's death row. By Rick
Bragg.
</P>
<P>
   AFFIRMATIVE-ACTION (Los Angeles) _ After watching black and
Hispanic enrollment tumble with the end of affirmative action,
University of California regents are expected Friday to officially
retool admissions, guaranteeing a spot for students in the top 4
percent of their high school class. The switch, heavily promoted by
Gov. Gray Davis, will bring in more rural and poor students and,
supporters hope it will serve as a morale booster for schools that
traditionally send few students to the university. By Dirk Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   MISSING-WOMEN (Long Barn, Calif.) _ The car of the three women
who have been missing for more than a month from Yosemite National
Park has been found, a burned hulk. By Evelyn Nieves.
