agrees to spend $3 billion to buy 40 percent of the Italian
producer of luxury goods. The French company, whose assets include
the La Redoute mail-order catalogue and the Fnac music chain, also
says that its Artemis holding company has bought Sanofi's beauty
business for $1 billion and will offer it to Gucci at the same
purchase price. By John Tagliabue.
