<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MCGRORY-COLUMN (Undated) _ He was a wisp of a man, really, small
in size but huge in stature, his very presence able to fill a room,
even an entire life, which was precisely Dr. Warren Nugent's
intent. By Brian McGrory.
</P>
<P>
   NYHAN-COLUMN (Undated) -- Singing the praises of a resurgent
Peace Corps. By David Nyhan.
</P>
<P>
   JACKSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ Trent Lott's excuses for racism. By
Derrick Jackson.
