</P>
<P>
   KABBALAH (Undated) _ For centuries, the study of the Kabbalah
could be undertaken only by married men over 40 who had already
mastered Jewish law. For anyone else the promised result was
insanity. Now we know otherwise. Roseanne Barr, one of the many who
has taken up the new Kabbalah fad, says that ``Before Kabbalah I
had no friends and everyone thought I was crazy.'' By Mervyn
Rothstein.
</P>
<P>
   DUCHAMP-HOAX (Undated) _ The influence of Marcel Duchamp's
readymades on 20th Century art is incalculable. But now an artist
has upset the art world by claiming they were an engineered hoax.
She says it's like discovering that ``there was no historical
Jesus.'' Critics say she's crazy. By Sarah Boxer.
</P>
<P>
   MARCEAU-DANCE (New York) _ ``3 Poor Souls'' with Marcel Marceau
is reviewed by Anna Kisselgoff.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   TV-POSSESSIONS-REVIEW (Undated) _ Anita Gates reviews ``Earthly
Possessions'' on HBO.
</P>
