<HEADLINE>
HEARST INVESTS IN INTERNET MEDICAL SITE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The Hearst Corporation has invested in Medscape, an
Internet site that provides information on diseases, medications,
treatments and access to articles on medical developments.
</P>
<P>
   Medscape is home to the largest medical community on the World
Wide Web, with over 1 million registered members, including
physicians, health care professionals and consumers.
</P>
<P>
   The site (www.medscape.com) offers free access to tens of
thousands of full-text articles from clinical journals, medical
news providers, medical education programs and material created
expressly for the service.
</P>
<P>
   One of Medscape's major content providers is First DataBank, a
wholly owned unit of The Hearst Corporation. First DataBank's
National Drug Data File covers every drug product approved by the
Food and Drug Administration for use in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   More than 240,000 drug records are available, each containing
information on ingredients, strength, dosage and other information.
</P>
<P>
   ``Medscape's leadership position and dedication to providing the
highest quality on-line medical content and interactive services to
physicians, allied health care professionals and consumers makes it
exactly the kind of company we want as a strategic partner,''
according to Kenneth A. Bronfin, a senior vice president for Hearst
New Media and Technology.
</P>
<P>
   Other companies investing in Medscape, a four-year-old company
based in New York, include Weston Presidio Capital and Highland
Capital Partners, both of which are Boston-based firms with
significant experience and investments in Internet and health care
markets.
</P>
<P>
   Hearst New Media and Technology is the unit of The Hearst
Corporation responsible for building and managing Hearst's
interests in new media and the technology that surrounds it. Hearst
manages a wide variety of consumer and business-related Internet
sites, including the recently formed Women.com Networks LLC.
</P>
<P>
   Hearst also holds equity stakes in a number of Internet-related
companies, including Broadcast.com, E Ink Corporation, Exodus
Communications, I/Pro, and Talk City.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst Corporation is one of the nation's largest
diversified communications companies, with interests in magazine,
newspaper, book and business publishing, television and radio
stations, newspaper comics and features syndication, cable
television networks, television production and syndication, and new
media activities.
</P>
</TEXT>
