   MEXICO-GUNS (Nuevo Laredo, Mexico) _ A new law calls for fines
instead of prison time for foreigners caught with a single shotgun
or low-caliber handgun, but it stiffens the penalties for most
handguns and rifles higher than .22 caliber because they are
reserved for use by the Mexican military. It is unclear how the law
will affect Christopher Colvin, 22, of Monroe, La. He is one of
scores of Americans jailed for violating Mexico's strict gun laws.
By DANE SCHILLER. (Already filed.)
