<SLUG> BC-CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JETTA IS JAZZY AND SNAZZY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New Beetle might be Volkswagen's image car, but the compact
Jetta sedan is the German automaker's bread-and-butter vehicle in
North America.
</P>
<P>
   The Jetta has long been VW's best-selling North American model,
but most people don't know that it's also the best-selling European
car on this continent.
</P>
<P>
   To help boost already great sales, the Jetta got a complete
makeover for 1999. Nearly everything is new or vastly improved
enough so that this fourth-generation Jetta is more like a luxury
car than an affordable compact.
</P>
<P>
   Beginning with the more rounded and elegant exterior, and
continuing through an interior that seems more Audi-luxury than
Volkswagen-simple, the Jetta is the best compact vehicle VW has
ever built.
</P>
<P>
   Add the performance of the optional 2.8-liter, 174-horsepower
VR6 engine, the rigidity of the body and suspension, and the sporty
five-speed manual gearbox, and the Jetta seems to be more sports
car than small sedan.
</P>
<P>
   Prices begin at $14,845 (plus $500 transportation) for the base
GL model with 2.0- liter, 115-horsepower four-cylinder engine. Even
the base car is well-equipped, coming with air-conditioning, front
and side air bags for the front-seat occupants, premium eight-
speaker AM/FM/cassette stereo, antilock brakes, tilt and telescopic
steering wheel, heated manual-remote-control mirrors, power door
locks, and more.
</P>
<P>
   Our test car was the midlevel GLS with the optional six-cylinder
engine, with a base price of $19,950 plus transportation. Amenities
added to the GLS include power windows and mirrors, cruise control
and a front center armrest.
</P>
<P>
   Top of the line GLX models come standard with the VR6 engine, as
well as automatic climate control, rain-sensor windshield wipers,
leather interior with wood trim, self-dimming rear-view mirror and
halogen headlights with fog lamps.
</P>
<P>
   For an extra $1,850, our test car came with a luxury package and
partial leather interior, the only options on the vehicle. Total
sticker was $22,325, including transportation, quite low for the
level of comfort and convenience features. This could very well be
the best compact-sedan bargain on the market: a near-luxury car for
less than $23,000.
</P>
<P>
   Driving the Jetta is more fun than riding in it. Sure, the back
seat is fairly roomy, and the front bucket seats are quite
comfortable, with adequate bolstering to keep driver and passenger
seated tightly during curves and turns.
</P>
<P>
   But with the speedy engine, tight steering and rigid body, the
Jetta's road handling abilities make it the embodiment of VW's
``Driver's Wanted'' advertising theme. Who says a sedan has to be
boring?
</P>
<P>
   Later this year, a 1.9-liter, 90-horsepower, four-cylinder
diesel engine will be available in the Jetta, with an EPA
fuel-economy rating of 49 miles per gallon on the highway.
</P>
<P>
   Even with the powerful six-cylinder engine in our test car, the
EPA ratings are a respectable 19 miles per gallon in the city and
26 on the highway. This is one speedy little car, but you don't
have to pay a huge penalty in fuel expense.
</P>
<P>
   My only complaint is that there is too much torque-steer in the
front wheels with the VR6 engine, a common problem in high-powered
front-wheel-drive vehicles. Torque-steer is the tendency to pull in
the direction of the drive wheel that is receiving power, rather
than going the direction the driver is trying to steer. It takes
some getting used to, especially when accelerating in curves and in
curves on rough road surfaces.
</P>
<P>
   The Jetta has lots of good safety features. Besides the antilock
brakes and side air bags, it has daytime running lights,
energy-absorbing crumple zones in the body structure, three-point
safety belts for all five seating positions, a collapsible steering
column, and adjustable headrests for all seats.
</P>
<P>
   The galvanized steel body has the longest corrosion warranty in
the industry: 12 years/unlimited mileage. The basic new-car
warranty covers everything for two years or 24,000 miles, and an
extended 10-year, 100,000-mile warranty covers the powertrain.
Scheduled maintenance, including oil changes, is covered free for
the first two years or 24,000 miles, whichever comes first.
</P>
<P>
   A four-speed automatic transmission is available for $860, but
who needs it? The Jetta is much more fun to drive with the manual
five-speed.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   At A Glance:
</P>
<P>
   1999 Volkswagen Jetta GLS VR6 sedan
</P>
<P>
   THE PACKAGE: Compact, four-door, five-passenger, V-6 powered,
front-drive sedan, completely redesigned for 1999.
</P>
<P>
   HIGHLIGHTS: With its 174-horsepower V-6, this is a speedy
compact sedan that is great fun to drive. Styling is more rounded
and aerodynamic than before, giving the car a much more elegant
look; the interior is well done, with obvious attention to detail.
And this is an affordable car that offers a lot more for the money
than many of its competitors.
</P>
<P>
   NEGATIVES: Noticeable torque-steer in curves and turns.
</P>
<P>
   MAJOR COMPETITORS: Ford Contour/Mercury Mystique, Pontiac Grand
Am, Oldsmobile Alero, Chevrolet Malibu, Acura Integra, Saab 9-3.
</P>
<P>
   EPA FUEL ECONOMY: 19 miles per gallon city, 26 highway.
</P>
<P>
   BASE PRICE: $19,950 plus $525 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   PRICE AS TESTED: $22,325, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   ON THE ROAD RATING: A.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (G. Chambers Williams III writes on transportation issues for
the Fort Worth Star-Telegram. His mailing address is
Star-Telegram/Northeast, 3201 Airport Freeway, Suite 108, Bedford,
Texas 76021; his E-mail address is chambers(at)star-telegram.com.
Fax: (817) 685-3883. Check out his Wheelin' new-car review column
weekly on the Internet at
ww.netarrant.net/today/news/opinions/necol.htm. Visit the
Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
