<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, March 19 --
The Pennsylvania State University of University Park won a $3.3
million contract from the Navy in Washington, D.C., for research
and development.
</P>
<P>
   Considine Biebel and Co. of Erie won a $471,000 contract from
the Navy in Lester for property maintenance and repair.
</P>
<P>
   Bean Construction Co. Inc. of Erie won a $83,444 contract from
the Coast Guard in Cleveland, Ohio, for property maintenance and
repair.
</P>
<P>
   Dentsply Trubyte of York won a $6.6 million cotnract from the
Dept. of Veterans Affairs in Hines, Ill., for dental equipment and
supplies.
</P>
<P>
   United Defense LP of York won a $8.7 million contract from the
Army in Warren, Mich., for ground effect vehicles.
</P>
<P>
   Advanced Automation Technologies of Exton won a $268,200
contract from the Army in St. Paul, Minn., for construction
equipment.
</P>
