veiled reference to Governor Paul Cellucci, says ``well-informed''
Catholics who support the deathy penalty are committing a sin. By
Diego Ribadeneira. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   NHAMP-TAX (Concord, N.H.) _ With time running out, not even a
committee controlled by Democrats can agree on an education tax
plan, rejecting a historic proposal calling for a combination
income tax and statewide property tax. By Ralph Jiminez. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   TUBMAN-STATUE (Boston) _ Harriet Tubman's portion of the
Underground Railroad aided many escaped slaves on their way to
Canada. This month, Boston honors the ex-slave with a statue that's
the first in the city of an African-American woman. By Cindy
Rodriquez. 800 words.
</P>
