<HEADLINE>
TOUGH GUYS NOT DANCING
</HEADLINE>
  
 Advance for Monday March 22  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Sean Penn &LR;  and  &UR; Nicolas Cage, &LR;  who once were pals, seem to be
on the outs.
</P>
<P>
   In a New York Times story a few months ago, Penn said that Cage
is no longer an ``actor'' but a ``performer.'' Then, in an
interview in Newsweek a few weeks ago, Penn called most Hollywood
movies ``abominable.'' Citing the movie ``Snake Eyes,'' which
starred Penn, he said he was ``appalled when talented actors debase
themselves. ... I think actors s_ on their profession all the time.
They can't do a pure movie again, because they carry so much
baggage.''
</P>
<P>
   Last week, during a Canadian press junket for ``8 MM,'' Cage
said he'd been upset about the remarks, particularly as they'd been
made after a friendly evening together. ``The door to our
friendship is now closed,'' said Cage, in remarks quoted in the New
York Post. ``In this business you get enough negativity from the
press without having your friends dump on you in public.''
</P>
<P>
   Penn's press representative said that as far as she knows, there
is ``no feud.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SHOPPING SPREE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Judy Reimann  &LR; doesn't understand TV ads for the animated
``King and I,'' which quote a critic saying ``At long last! A `King
and I' for the whole family!'' Reimann says she must have missed
the adult version starring  &UR; Jeff Stryker  &LR; and  &UR; Dirk &LR; 
 &UR; Diggler &LR; ; furthermore, the ads give new meaning to ``Whenever I
feel afraid, I hold my head erect, and whistle a happy tune.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Richard O'Lone  &LR; is worried about Eligibility Rule No. 4 for
ClickRewards, an internet site wherein shoppers accumulate frequent
flier miles for merchandise bought: ``Members must be human.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Antigua and Barbuda have issued a new set of postage stamps
featuring Australian supermodel  &UR; Elle Macpherson &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   _ Advertising Age says that KFC, Pizza Hut and Taco Bell will
spend $50 million on ads relating to ``Star Wars'' merchandise
they'll be hawking.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Matt White &LR;  recently signed up for Green Mountain Energy
Resources, an environmentally aware power company, in appreciation
for which he was sent two beeswax candles. Is this a portent of the
company's efficiency? he asks.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hurdle that problem:  &UR; Dan Dorritie &LR; 's pal just got a new PC,
with all times and clock pre-set, to March 17, 2099.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HOME TOWN NOTES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ San Francisco Mayor  &UR; Willie Brown &LR;  (on his way to a trade
mission in Africa),  &UR; George &LR;  and  &UR; Charlotte Shultz &LR; ,  &UR; Tom Horn  &LR; and
a gaggle of other civic leaders will be at the opening of the
Exploradome in Paris on March 31. The new facility, in the Bois de
Boulogne, will feature 35 exhibits based on exhibits at the
Exploratorium in San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   _ Earthquake commemoration ceremonies will be, as always, on
Sunday, April 18, on the site of Lotta's Fountain. Survivors are
invited the Friday before to a Bay tour aboard a Golden Gate
Transit ferry, and lunch at John's Grill (to which they should RSVP
beforehand).
</P>
<P>
   _ Guests are implored ``Do not bring guns,'' to the April 10
Precita Park Gun Bake organized by Peaceful Streets. Blacksmiths
will melt down guns previously turned in, turning them into
one-half of a memorial bench for a couple killed last year in
Precita Park. The other half of the bench will be made from guns
turned in after the event.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Paula Jones &LR;  and her husband are living in separate places,
but she insists they are not separated.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Wavy Gravy &LR; , renowned artist and clown, has a show of
collages at the Firehouse Gallery in Bordentown, N.J. from April 3
to 26.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; David Jensen  &LR; forwards a copy of the San Francisco Unified
School District's Profile of Lowell High School that cites excused
and unexcused ``absenses.'' ``Why is everyone trying so hard to get
in this place?'' he asks, but we are pinning the blame on the
District.
</P>
