<SLUG> BC-DEPOT20-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Office Depot head gets 14% pay raise, plus bonus
 &HT;    By Julie Waresh
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DELRAY BEACH, Fla. _ Office Depot Inc. boosted Chief Executive
David Fuente's base pay by nearly 14 percent to $1 million last
year as the company's performance continued to surpass
expectations.
</P>
<P>
   On top of that, Fuente received a bonus of just more than $2
million in 1998 _ up from almost $1.8 million the year before.
</P>
<P>
   Fuente also received options to buy 1 million shares of Office
Depot (NYSE: ODP) stock at $29.59 a share, according to the
company's proxy, filed Friday with the Securities and Exchange
Commission.
</P>
<P>
   Fuente's other compensation, which included medical and life
insurance and an automobile allowance, amounted to $215,180. Based
on Friday's closing price of $36 a share, Fuente's total
compensation package was worth $9.7 million.
</P>
<P>
   His 1997 compensation package, worth more than $11 million when
it was disclosed, included stock options set at prices in the $13
to $16 range.
</P>
<P>
   The office products retailer, which has more than 700 stores,
showered executives with options that year in an effort to retain
them after the collapse of its agreement to be bought by rival
Staples Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Since then, Office Depot's performance has exceeded projections.
The giant retailer last month reported earnings of $1.24 a share
for 1998 _ a penny above the market consensus.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
