NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, MARCH 20
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CHINA-NUKE-NYT (moved on Thursday, Mar. 18)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Mar. 18,
about the House's passage of a bill to create a missile defense
system misstated the final vote. It was 317 to 105, not 371 to 105.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-BARNETT (moved on Thursday, Mar. 18)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of A. Doak Barnett, sent by the New York Times News
Service on moved on Thursday, Mar. 18, misstated the day of his
death. It was Wednesday, not Monday.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-GEEK-NOTES-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Mar. 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Mar.
17, referred incorrectly to a recall by the Iomega Corporation. It
affects the power supply units of some external Jaz disk drives,
not the drives themselves.
</P>
