<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    How St. John's stacks up against Ohio State
 &HT;    By Jack Wilkinson
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   When; where: 6 p.m. today; Thompson-Boling Arena, Knoxville.
</P>
<P>
   TV: CBS.
</P>
<P>
   Records: St. John's 28-8, Ohio State 26-8.
</P>
<P>
   Coaches: Mike Jarvis is 28-8 in his first season at St. John's,
281-149 overall; Jim O'Brien is 34-30 in two seasons at Ohio State,
269-247 overall.
</P>
<P>
   How they got here: St. John's, the third seed, crushed Samford
69-43 in the first round, gave Indiana its worst NCAA Tournament
loss 86-61, then ousted second-seeded Maryland 76-62 in the
regional semifinals. Ohio State, the fourth seed, beat Murray State
72-58 in the first round, blew out Detroit 75-44, then broke a
61-61 tie with nine consecutive points to upset top-seeded Auburn
72-64.
</P>
<P>
   Possible lineups: St. John's _ guards, Erick Barkley (6-1, Fr.,
13.2 ppg) and Bootsy Thornton (6-4, Jr., 14.7); center, Tyrone
Grant (6-7, Sr., 10.8 ppg); forwards, Ron Artest (6-7, Soph., 14.8
ppg) and Lavor Postell (6-6, Jr., 12.9 ppg). Ohio State _ guards,
Scoonie Penn (5-10, Jr., 16.7 ppg) and Brian Brown (6-3, Fr., 3.9
ppg); center, Ken Johnson (6-11, Jr., 6.3 ppg); forwards, Michael
Redd (6-6, Soph., 19.7 ppg) and Jason Singleton (6-5, Sr., 8.8
ppg).
</P>
<P>
   Outlook: Ohio State has completed a remarkable turnaround from
year's abysmal 8-22 finish, and St. John's _ upset by Detroit in
the first round last year _ has flourished under new coach Mike
Jarvis. Both have won 11 of 13, each losing in its conference
tournament. Both have played terrific defense in the NCAAs
</P>
<P>
   Prediction: St. John's 73-71.
</P>
